n with brother Roger","body":"He was twin to Abner Newton Jr., born together October 23, 1726 in the Durham Main Street house. After the Revolution he removed to Greenfield, Massachusetts, where his brother Rev. Roger Newton was minister for 53 years."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Hemlock swamps that became valuable land","body":"He, his son Isaac, and his brother Roger purchased many acres of wild land in Greenfield at 7 shillings 6 pence per acre. The hemlock swamp later became valuable; he held many civic offices in the town after the war."},{"number":4,"category":"death","header":"His second wife died two weeks before him","body":"His second wife Hulda died September 14, 1802 in Greenfield, age 60. He died two weeks later on September 28, age nearly 76."}],"slug":"john-newton-1726"},"neighborhood":{"focus":{"id":"H00148","slug":"john-newton-1726","n":"John Newton","by":1726,"dy":1802,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":5},"spouses":[{"order":1,"spouse":{"id":"I00082","slug":"mary-pickett","n":"Mary Pickett Newton","by":null,"dy":1786,"sx":"f","hd":false,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":null},"year":null,"children":[{"id":"HD0154","slug":"isaac-newton-1748","n":"Captain Isaac Newton","by":1748,"dy":1824,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0155","slug":"john-newton-1750","n":"John Newton","by":1750,"dy":null,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0156","slug":"samuel-newton-1752","n":"Samuel Newton","by":1752,"dy":null,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0157","slug":"comfort-newton-1755","n":"Comfort Newton","by":1755,"dy":null,"sx":"u","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0158","slug":"stephen-newton-1756","n":"Stephen Newton","by":1756,"dy":null,"sx":"m","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0159","slug":"sarah-newton-1758","n":"Sarah Newton","by":1758,"dy":null,"sx":"f","hd":true,"td":false,"ee":false,"g":6},{"id":"HD0160","slug":"rhoda-newton-1760","n":"Rhoda Newt